 Auto-seeded entries are updated on each pool load — if you remove an env var, its pool entry is automatically pruned. Manual entries (added via `hermes auth add`) are never auto-pruned.
 
+### Multiple Claude Code accounts
+
+Anthropic pool rows can bind to separate Claude Code config directories. Add one metadata-only row per account to the active profile's `auth.json` (for example `~/.hermes/profiles/<profile>/auth.json`):
+
+```json
+{
+  "credential_pool": {
+    "anthropic": [
+      {
+        "id": "cc-work",
+        "label": "Claude work",
+        "auth_type": "oauth",
+        "priority": 0,
+        "source": "claude_code",
+        "claude_config_dir": "~/.claude-work"
+      },
+      {
+        "id": "cc-personal",
+        "label": "Claude personal",
+        "auth_type": "oauth",
+        "priority": 1,
+        "source": "claude_code",
+        "CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR": "~/.claude-personal"
+      }
+    ]
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Both `claude_config_dir` and `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` are accepted on input. Hermes normalizes the field to `claude_config_dir` and assigns each non-default directory a stable `claude_code:<hash>` source id. On macOS it reads Claude Code's directory-scoped Keychain service; elsewhere it reads `<claude_config_dir>/.credentials.json`. Access and refresh tokens remain borrowed from Claude Code and are not copied into `auth.json`.
+
+The process-level `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` remains the backward-compatible single-account default. Explicit pool rows are what enable several Claude Code accounts in one Hermes profile and one rotation pool.
+
+Claude Code-sourced rows use the official streaming Claude Code agent runtime automatically. Claude Code owns its native Bash/file/subagent loop while Hermes relays partial output, persists the completed tool history, and exposes enabled Hermes/profile MCP tools through a local stdio bridge. API-key-only Anthropic rows continue to use the Messages API. Set `model.anthropic_runtime: native` to force the Messages path, or `claude_code` to select the agent runtime explicitly (`claude_code_cli` remains a compatibility alias).
+
+On a 401/429 before any tool starts, Hermes can rotate to the next config directory and retry. Once a native tool has started, Hermes does not replay the turn because doing so could duplicate file or command side effects.
+
 Borrowed runtime secrets (for example env vars, Bitwarden/Vault/keyring/systemd references, and custom config values) are reference-only at the `auth.json` boundary. Hermes can use the resolved value in memory for the current run, but it persists only metadata such as the source ref, label, status, request counters, and a non-reversible fingerprint. Manual entries and Hermes-owned OAuth/device-code state keep the durable tokens they need to refresh.
 
